From: Stelios Tsampas <loathingkernel@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 23 Jun 2026 12:40:43 +0300
Subject: [PATCH 7/8] upscalers: add optiscaler downloader

Config values are passed through the `PROTON_OPTISCALER_CONFIG` environment
variable. The config is a semicolon (`;`) separated string of individual options.
For each option the template is `{header}.{option}={value}`, i.e to set the following
```
[Upscalers]
Dx11Upscaler=fsr31
Dx12Upscaler=dlss
```
the config should be
```
PROTON_OPTISCALER_CONFIG="Upscalers.Dx11Upscaler=fsr31;Upscalers.Dx12Upscaler=dlss"`
```

To avoid mistakes, config options should already exist in `Optiscaler.ini`.

The changes are to the config are permanent, it has to be either manually edited or
a different config should be applied through the env variable.

Using this will also remove any comments from the `OptiScaler.ini` file.
